{"id":1734829,"retrievedAt":"2026-07-21T12:46:59.905Z","response":{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":null,"belongs_to_collection":null,"budget":0,"genres":[],"homepage":"","id":1734829,"imdb_id":null,"origin_country":["US"],"original_language":"en","original_title":"Jurnal Suraya","overview":"# Suraya's Journal  The story depicts Suraya's (Nad Zainal) perseverance in continuing her life as a leukemia patient. The strength that Suraya possesses to face her daily life while trying to complete her studies is admired by her friends who share the same condition. Besides her friends, Alif (Johan As'ari), who suffers from stage three bone cancer, also quietly admires the woman. The relationship between Suraya and Alif is initially limited to close friendship only because Suraya's father, Datuk Hisham (Khairi Anwar), wants to marry Suraya to Imran (Ryzal Jaafar). However, Imran has a hidden agenda behind his seriousness to marry Suraya—to acquire Suraya's family wealth. Nevertheless, Imran's deception is seen through by Suraya because she knows his true nature of indulging in nightclubs. Suraya's illness forces her to go to Singapore for treatment, which is a last-ditch effort on her doctor's, Dr. Nadia's, recommendation.","popularity":0.0071,"poster_path":"/h1P1uoeQFweQHCnRkanussur9GW.jpg","production_companies":[],"production_countries":[],"release_date":"2017-01-01","revenue":0,"runtime":0,"softcore":false,"spoken_languages":[],"status":"Released","tagline":"","title":"Jurnal Suraya","video":false,"vote_average":0,"vote_count":0,"alternative_titles":{"titles":[]},"credits":{"cast":[{"adult":false,"gender":1,"id":1292088,"known_for_department":"Acting","name":"Nad Zainal","original_name":"Nad Zainal","popularity":0.3962,"profile_path":"/chhdcOGnyAu3vLgOzOhT1OBBfen.jpg","cast_id":2,"character":"","credit_id":"6a5e6ec603f6533a304f6138","order":0},{"adult":false,"gender":2,"id":1271796,"known_for_department":"Acting","name":"Johan As'ari","original_name":"Johan As'ari","populari